Explore the area

Get to know Auckland City

Auckland City encompasses many of the smaller suburbs surrounding the central business district in the city centre.

As New Zealand’s most populous metropolitan area, the city is at the heart of all activity in the wider region. Even so, the suburbs within Auckland City each offer something different: from relaxed neighbourhoods filled with beautiful green spaces to the dynamic inner-city areas perfect for those in search of a city-centre lifestyle.

As such, Auckland City is a diverse, friendly and modern place to live, with the urban area attracting students, workers and families alike.

The plethora of bars, cafes, beaches and parks is enough to keep even the most active of people busy. But for those who fancy a short break-away from the city, Auckland is within reach of several black sand beaches on the West Coast, Cape Reinga and the surrounding Northland region, or the equally impressive Coromandel peninsula to the East.

Plus, with a wide variety of schools and universities, sports teams and stadiums, art museums, quirky markets, new transport links and more, it’s no surprise to hear that Auckland is regularly named as one of the most liveable cities in the world.

Auckland City encompasses many of the smaller suburbs surrounding the central business district in the city centre.
